sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Spark Operator Controller<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod<br/>7078,7079/TCP
    participant Executors as Spark Executor Pods
    participant ConnectSrv as Spark Connect Server<br/>15002/TCP gRPC
    participant Ingress as Kubernetes Ingress<br/>80/443 HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Client as Client Application

    Note over User,Executors: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkApplication CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-sparkapplication<br/>HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Defaulted SparkApplication<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-sparkapplication<br/>HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch SparkApplication CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: SparkApplication Event

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>Inject config, volumes, env vars
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Pod Spec

    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token (spark SA)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>Inject executor config
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Executor Spec

    Executors->>Driver: driver-rpc<br/>7078/TCP plaintext
    Executors->>Driver: blockmanager<br/>7079/TCP plaintext

    Note over User,Client: Flow 2: Spark Connect Session

    User->>K8sAPI: POST SparkConnect CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Server Pod, Service, ConfigMap<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Client->>ConnectSrv: gRPC Request<br/>15002/TCP plaintext
    ConnectSrv->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,Ingress: Flow 3: Spark Web UI Access

    User->>Ingress: GET Spark UI<br/>80/443 HTTP/HTTPS
    Ingress->>Driver: Forward to Spark UI<br/>4040/TCP HTTP plaintext
    Driver-->>Ingress: Spark UI HTML
    Ingress-->>User: Spark UI Response

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 4: ScheduledSparkApplication

    Controller->>Controller: Cron Trigger
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create SparkApplication<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Note right of K8sAPI: Follows Flow 1 from step 4
